          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A value of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "0.0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " (the default) or less specifies no chamfer—the extruded sides of each character end at right angles to its front and back."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The maximum chamfer radius is half the value of the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scntext/1522604-extrusiondepth"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property. At this radius, the front chamfer ends where the back chamfer begins. However, SceneKit may automatically reduce the chamfer radius for character shapes with thin strokes."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can animate changes to this property’s value. See "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/animation/animating_scenekit_content"
            },
            {
